text: (electronic music)
- My name is Brian Kane,

and I lead a partner
business development team

focusing on our software
partnerships at AWS.

At AWS, when you think
about our partnerships

with software companies,
first and foremost,
they're customers of AWS.

That means that they've built
a solution on top of AWS.

And the team that I
lead focuses on co-sell.

Co-sell is when we work
together with our partners

to jointly bring a solution
to an end customer.
AWS is a builder culture,

and a lot of people
think that builder means

that you actually have to
write code or build a product.
In my role and in my team,

the focus is on building
relationships and building success
for the partners that we serve.

At AWS, you're encouraged
to come up with innovative

solutions that deliver
results and delight customers.

I've personally seen
people that I work with

come up with ideas, and those
quickly become teams and,

over the course of time,
entire organizations.
So if you're considering AWS,

the question that I would ask
yourself is, am I a builder?
Do I want to be a part of an environment
where I get the best of being at a startup
as well as the power and the impact

of being able to be at
a company of AWS's size?
